[b]Compression Fractal Release [WavesUnchained][/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
Compression Fractal Release (CFR) finds a compressed, corrective coil inside a higher-timeframe trend and signals the moment that coil resolves into a clean directional break — the release. The break of the prior correction band is the only trigger; how tightly the market was coiled and how decisively it is resolving are scored as weighted evidence, and a choppiness veto filters low-quality breaks. The higher-timeframe regime decides whether a break is a trend continuation (Release) or a structural change out of a base (Base Break).

[b]How it reads the market[/b]
[list]
[*]Compression complexity — bar returns are symbolised into five states in ATR steps, then state entropy is combined with the transition rate: high = busy/corrective, low = clean/directional.
[*]Box-counting fractal dimension — 1 = smooth/trend, 1.5+ = jagged/range.
[*]Efficiency — net displacement versus total path length; low efficiency + high complexity = a wound spring.
[*]Choppiness Index — an independent quality sensor used only as a veto.
[/list]

[b]Scoring[/b]
[list]
[*]Coil strength combines complexity, fractal dimension and inverse efficiency into a 0–1 reading.
[*]Release dynamics measure complexity falling and efficiency rising on the break bar.
[*]The Setup Score multiplies coil strength by the release dynamics, so a high coil alone cannot fire — a real release is required. A break fires only when the score clears the threshold, choppiness is below the veto, and a per-direction cooldown has elapsed.
[/list]

[b]Signals[/b]
[list]
[*]Release up / down — coil released in the higher-timeframe trend direction (continuation).
[*]Base Break up / down — break against the trend out of a prior base (structural change; needs more evidence).
[*]Setup Watch — coiled, trend-aligned and near the break band, not yet broken.
[/list]

[b]Display[/b]
[list]
[*]Regime background: clean trend, correction/coil, base.
[*]Break bands from the prior correction window.
[*]Light-theme dashboard: state, HTF trend, Setup Score, coil, release dynamics, compression, fractal dimension, choppiness.
[/list]

